{
  "texts": [
    "In this range, global interactions are consistently observed to improve reconstruction over self-only decoding without drifting into destructive or chaotic mixing.",
    "ViT-B achieves the highest pivot efficiency: a 34.1% task probe gain while InfoX drops from 0.127 to 0.085, and simultaneously converges to the best geometric quality (lowest NC2).",
    "ViT-L enters a regime of chaotic diffusion.",
    "Its Scrambling Index increases monotonically through depth, rising about 4.4× from layer 12 (0.007) to layer 23 (0.031).",
    "In this high-scrambling regime, cross-patch mixing is very strong, but the additional layers yield only marginal probe improvements (+1.3%) while degrading the final Neural Collapse geometry."
  ]
}